President Trump and Prime Minister Modi of India exchange remarks during a reception at the White House. They express gratitude for the invitation and discuss the warm relationship between the two countries. The Prime Minister thanks the First Lady for organizing the reception, which he sees as an honor for the people of India. President Trump mentions that the timing of the visit was adjusted due to elections in India, and congratulates the Prime Minister on his party's victory. The event concludes with thanks and appreciation from both leaders.